The paper discusses the fundamentals and recent advances in recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in various fields such as natural language processing (NLP), computer vision, and speech recognition. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories as they are directly related to RNNs. Additionally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as RNNs are a popular tool in AI research. The paper also mentions NLP, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language), and computer vision, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), making them less likely but still possible categories.
